This reference design contains the following contents:

1. kernels

   This folder contains the Vitis kernel projects which include the DPU
   inference engine RTL kernel and HLS-based computer vision kernels based on
   the Vitis Vision libraries. Follow the README inside this folder for detailed
   build instructions.

2. Makefile

   Top-level Makefile for building the Vitis platforms and kernel projects.
   Type 'make' or 'make help' to print the help text explaining the different
   make targets.

3. platforms

   This folder contains the KV260 Vitis platforms. Follow the REAMDE inside this
   folder for build instructions.

   Note: To build platforms make sure to set the Vivado Board Preset using the
         following steps

         1. git clone https://github.com/Xilinx/XilinxBoardStore
         2. Add the following line to Vivado initialization script
            set_param board.repoPaths {<path to the git repo>/boards/Xilinx}

            The initialization tcl script for Vivado can be found at:
            $HOME/.Xilinx/Vivado/Vivado_init.tcl

4. README

   This file.
